Linear Equation Class:




instance variables:
private int x1 - x coordinate
private int y1 - y coordinate
private int x2 - x coordinate
private int y2 - y coordinate




Constructor:
public LinearEquation(int x, int y){
}
construct an object using user input




Methods:




public double getYIntercept()
Will calculate the y intercept using the x and y values inputted




public double getSlope()
Will calculate slope and return slope




public double getDistance()
Will use distance formula to calculate distance between two points




public String getLinearEquation()
will return linear equation of the two points


public String getYForX()
will return the coordinate of the x value inputted by user


private String formatFraction()
will format a double value as a string and will return that string


public String toString()
will display all the information about the equation




Equation Runner:
1 - ask for x1 y1 coord using scanners
2 - ask for x2 y2 coord using scanners
3 - use indexOf and substring methods in order to extract the x and y values out of the parentheses and will also use the trim() method in order to not include any parentheses or commas in the x or y value.
4 - will use linearequation method to construct the two points
5 - display information using toString() method
6 - ask for  3rd x value and then use getYForX()
7 - display new point

